==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the {{Gr.}} ''[[καλλίπυγος]]'',  from ''[[καλός]]'' "beautiful" + ''[[πυγή]]'' "buttocks"

===Pronunciation===
*{{SAMPA|/"k{l.I.%pI.dZ@s/}}
*{{IPA|/'kæl.ɪ.ˌpɪ.dʒəs/}}

=== Adjective ===
'''callipygous'''
# Having [[shapely]], beautiful [[buttocks]].
#: ''He enjoyed Nurse Sue Ann Duckett's long white legs and supple, '''callipygous''' ass...'' - ''[[Catch-22]]'', [[Joseph Heller]].

